            "text": "1Kings 8:65",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). Hamath was the seat of an ancient kingdom, independent of, but friendly to David. The prophet Amos (eighth century B.C. ) calls it Hamath Rabbah, Great Hamath (",
