        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", from the Greek; Virgil, 'Georg.,' 4:278, 291; Catullus, 67:33). There can surely be little doubt that it is the river Nile which is here spoken of, after comparison of the following passages: - ",
