        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of Damascus, more resembling the nature of the mountain stream. This river was to the ancient Romans \"the representative of Syria, as the Timings might be said to be of England, and in later times the region formed the chief point of contact between this part of Asia and the West\" (Stanley's 'Sinai and Palestine,' pp. 414, ",
